olor=#A62A2A>(2/17/02 8:05:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1343.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pickpocketing</span><hr size=1> One thing you can try is to give them something worthless, like a bat wing.  My understanding is that items given to a creature go into their inventory in order, and you pick their inventory from the top down.  So, if you pick the item you have given them, then you have gone through the inventory.  A nice way to know if you are wasting your time.  <br>
<br>
Grymmas <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usilaena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silaena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/18/02 5:36:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1343.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pickpocketing</span><hr size=1> I disagree with the &quot;item at the end&quot; rule on pickpocket, it happend to me many time to get item far before I took all the coins. I think it is all in % of succes to get item that is much harder than coins. <br>
<br>
For exemple, there is not so long time when I were on another server, I pickpocketed the part of scroll from founy in Kaladim on my 1st attempt.. Lucky ?? yes , I guess it was a lucky attempt.<br>
<br>
